<body>
    <h1>SailPoint Manage Access Approval</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"SailPointManageAccessApproval-Overview">Overview</h3>
<p>SailPoint Manage Access Approval is a feature that enables organizations=
 to manage access approvals in a centralized and automated manner. Here's a=
n overview:</p>
<p>Key Features</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Access Requests</strong>: Manage access requests from users, inc=
luding requests for new access, changes to existing access, or removal of a=
ccess.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Approval Workflows</strong>: Define approval workflows that spec=
ify the sequence of approvals required for access requests.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Approver Management</strong>: Identify and manage approvers, inc=
luding their roles, responsibilities, and notification settings.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Automated Approvals</strong>: Automate approvals based on predef=
ined rules and conditions, reducing manual effort and improving efficiency.=
</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"SailPointManageAccessApproval-Scope">Scope</h3>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">The scope of this white paper is very spe=
cific to Voyager IAM team, w.r.t. SailPoint Identity IQ manage access imple=
mentation.</p>
<h3 id=3D"SailPointManageAccessApproval-ApproverManagement"><strong>Approve=
r Management</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Approval Mode</strong> is Serial</p>
<p><strong>Approval Scheme</strong> (Manager, Owner, Security Officer)<br>
Manager Approval is always first, followed by owner and Security Officer.</=
p>
<p>Manager -&gt; Owner (Role /App) -&gt; Security Officer</p>
<p><strong>Manager </strong>( always the requestee=E2=80=99s reporting mana=
ger) , is the first level of approver</p>
<p><strong>Owner</strong> ( Owner of role / entitlement / application ), if=
 configured owner will be the second level of approver</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Owner of role/entitlement takes priority if configured on Role or Entitl=
ement.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Owner of application takes priority if the role ownership is not defined=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p>It is recommended to use the workgroups ( group of people, min of 2 peop=
le) as owners instead of a single person, having 2 people in a workgroup wi=
ll eliminate the need of maintain the separate escalation workgroups.</p></=
li>
<li>
<p>Leaver workflow should consider the ownerships, pending workitems and ta=
ke appropriate actions, to identify the replacing ownerships.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Security Officer </strong>, is the 3rd and final level of approv=
er if configured.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"57=
674de3-3d6a-4284-9708-222847ddd63e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#4c9aff" colspan=3D"4" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p style=3D"text-align: center;"><strong>Approval Levels</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Level 0</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Level 1</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Level 2</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Level 3</strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>none</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Manager</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Role / Entitlement / Application Owner</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Security Officer</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"1c=
4307ad-f4e7-4191-8a7b-f6fae4fac17e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 335.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 424.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td data-highlight-colour=3D"#4c9aff" colspan=3D"2" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Approval Scheme &amp; Hierarchy </strong></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>none</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>no approvals needed</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>manager</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Manager approval only</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>manager, owner</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Manager approval followed by owner</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>manager, owner, securityofficer</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>manager approval followed by owner and then security officer</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"SailPointManageAccessApproval-Escalations"><strong>Escalations </=
strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>No escalations recommended for Manage Access Requests, in case to implem=
ent escalation at manager level, then the manager levels , executive manage=
rs and their delegates need to be taken into account.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Escalations are recommended for the Manager Level certifications ( Acces=
s Reviews), as there will be a reporting supervisor to follow up or take th=
e ownership of the certificate and complete it for audit requirements.</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>Maintaining escalation owners for approver workgroups is a custom proces=
s, that requires custom workflows. And to maintain these workgroups, proper=
 policies and procedures are needed and to be well defined. All correspondi=
ng parties need to be educated with the application and procedures.</p></li=
>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SailPointManageAccessApproval-Notifications"><strong>Notification=
s </strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Initial notifications <br>
Requestee &amp; Requester should receive the initial notification , notifyi=
ng that the access is requested or Revoked.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Approving manager/owner/Security Officer , should receive the workitem n=
otification with the link to the approval workitem.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Requestee and Requester should be notified upon completion ( approved or=
 rejected or expired)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Notification Reminders : 7, 14, 21 , 28 day notifications .</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>21 &amp; 28 day reminders should CC the requestee and requester.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>31 expiry notification</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Manager approval workitem assignment</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>If the approving manager is an executive manager, then check for delegat=
ion and assign the approval work item. <br><strong>Note: </strong>Delegatio=
n framework and delegation assignment is a different topic altogether , nee=
d to be discussed under delegation management bucket.</p></li>
<li>
<p>If a manager is terminated, the workitem need to be reassigned to the su=
pervisor. If the supervisor is an executive manager, reassign the workitem =
to the delegate.</p></li>
<li>
<p>If a manager is terminated, the workitem need to be expired . If the sup=
ervisor is an executive manager, and no delegate found.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
