<h3 id=3D"SailPointManageAccessApproval-BreakGlass">BreakGlass</h3>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Break glass procedure need to be well def=
ined and followed external to the SailPoint application, this is a manual p=
rocedure: senior level manager and corresponding approval paper work need t=
o be discussed and documented outside of this forum, as each application ha=
s a respective ownership and procedures.</p>
<h3 id=3D"SailPointManageAccessApproval-DelegationFramework">Delegation Fra=
mework</h3>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">SailPoint IdentityIQ Delegation Managemen=
t enables organizations to delegate administrative tasks and responsibiliti=
es to specific users or groups. This feature allows for more efficient mana=
gement of identity and access governance. This need to be further discussed=
 and outline the implementation procedures.</p>
<p><strong>Workgroup Management</strong></p>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Workgroup management typically refers to =
the process of managing teams or groups within an organization. In the cont=
ext of SailPoint IdentityIQ, workgroup management might involve: Defining t=
he Workgroups, add/remove members, sync the members based on their JML even=
ts. This need to be further discussed and automate the implementation.</p>
